text:
At some point in this history I was asked to join a band called Vintage who I was with until after I left school. Vintage were a very strange combination.

In that band we had S on guitar, C on bass, RB on drums, and me on vocals, no keyboard.
name: Marx "Timelily" Shepherd {they/them}

text: At some point we had this amazing little band with B on guitar, C on bass, G on guitar, J on drums, and me doing vocals. We played two ska tracks extremely competently and brought the house down in a talent contest.
name: Marx "Timelily" Shepherd {they/them}

text: The year after M (guitar), L (bass), and me (keys and vocals?) tried out a band that we thought was cool for not having a name or a drummer. We used to practice in my living room. I think we played The Warmth (sorry, forgot the band) and Paradise City. Weird choices.
name: Marx "Timelily" Shepherd {they/them}

text: I think in Year 9 we had another band, but I don't remember the name. We definitely had J on drums, G on guitar, me on keys and vocals, and my friend L on bass. L was friends with this girl I was crushing hard on at that time so it was essential that we impressed her.
name: Marx "Timelily" Shepherd {they/them}

text: Next up is Birnam Wood. Fans of Shakespeare will know where I got that name from. We had J on drums, G on guitar, and me on vocals and keys. G had just started playing guitar so our chord repertoire was limited, but what we lacked in skill we made up for in...
name: Marx "Timelily" Shepherd {they/them}
